<subSubSection id="C3496558FFBEFFB4FF2FB833FCFDF896" pageId="5" pageNumber="539" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BEC36D3FFBEFFB4FF2FB833FC6AF8AA" blockId="5.[151,1437,1593,1907]" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">
Type data: This species was described based on four females from 
<collectingCountry id="F3447643FFBEFFB4FC3BB833FC52F9B6" box="[899,954,1593,1619]" name="Peru" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">Peru</collectingCountry>
. In 
<collectionCode id="ED42AE16FFBEFFB4FC5BB833FBD1F9B6" box="[995,1081,1593,1619]" country="Hungary" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">HNHM</collectionCode>
I found one female collected in “Yurimagua” and another one from “Tebas”. Both specimens must belong to the type series and are here designated 
<typeStatus id="54E88871FFBEFFB4FF2FB88BFF16F97E" box="[151,254,1665,1691]" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">lectotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="54E88871FFBEFFB4FE80B88BFE3AF97E" box="[312,466,1665,1691]" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">paralectotype</typeStatus>
, respectively. 
<typeStatus id="54E88871FFBEFFB4FDCCB88BFD0CF97E" box="[628,740,1665,1691]" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">Lectotype</typeStatus>
with the following data label: [light greenish square without text]\ Yurimaguas [handwritten] Brasilia [printed]\ [black-rimmed] 685. 60. [handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D50FFBEFFB4FB20B8AFFA75F95A" authority="Typ. Mocs." authorityName="Typ. Mocs." box="[1176,1437,1701,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulviventris">
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBEFFB4FB20B8AFFAFEF95A" box="[1176,1302,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">fulviventris</emphasis>
Typ. Mocs.
</taxonomicName>
[handwritten]. 
<typeStatus id="54E88871FFBEFFB4FE86B8C3FE3EF906" box="[318,470,1737,1763]" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">Paralectotype</typeStatus>
with the following data label: [purple square label without text]\ Tebas [handwritten] Brasilia [printed]\ [black-rimmed] 685. 60. [handwritten]. According to the accession book at 
<collectionCode id="ED42AE16FFBEFFB4FB08B8E7FAEEF8E2" box="[1200,1286,1773,1799]" country="Hungary" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">HNHM</collectionCode>
the 
<typeStatus id="54E88871FFBEFFB4FA8EB8E7FA75F8E2" box="[1334,1437,1773,1799]" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">lectotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="54E88871FFBEFFB4FF7EB91BFEB5F8CE" box="[198,349,1809,1835]" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">paralectotype</typeStatus>
were purchased from insect dealer Otto Staudinger in 1884. The current condition and depository of the remaining type specimens, now 
<typeStatus id="54E88871FFBEFFB4FDF0B93FFD05F8AA" box="[584,749,1845,1871]" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
, is unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC36D3FFBEFFB4FF7FB953FCFDF896" blockId="5.[151,1437,1593,1907]" box="[199,789,1881,1907]" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">
